def top_3(data, parameter):
    year_list = data["year"].dt.year.sort_values().unique()
    result_df = pd.DataFrame(columns=year_list,index=[1,2,3])
    
    # filling the above given dataframe with the help of for loop
    for year in year_list:
        df_year = data[data["year"].dt.year==year]
        value = df_year.groupby("country")[parameter].sum().sort_values(ascending=False).head(3).index
        result_df[year] = value
        
    return(result_df)

Inference/Conclusion¶

  1. Inflation rate: Amongst the G20 countries since 2017 country "Turkiye" has the highest inflation.

  2. Unemployment rate is the highest in South Africa over the period between 2015 to 2020.

  3. Mexico, Argentina and Italy are the top 3 countries in terms of poverty rate in the year 2020.

  4. Over the period of five years between 2015 to 2020 Japan tops the list among the G20 countries in terms of Life Expectancy.

  5. We could observe that South Africa, Saudi Arabia and Indonesia have spend the most on Education over the past five years.

  6. Among all the G20 countries Germany and Mexico Exports more goods and services to the world for the period between 2015 to 2020. At the same time these two countries are also the largest importers of goods and services.

  7. China tops the list in terms of Gross Capital Formation for the period between 2015 to 2020. China has managed to maintain its position at the top since these five year period.

  8. In terms of Agricultural land area, Saudi Arabia followed by South Africa and then United Kingdom are the top three countries continuously for the period between 2015-2020.

  9. The GDP and GNI is the highest for United States followed by China and then Japan among all the G20 countries for 2015-2020.

  10. The percentage change in FDI is highest for Japan, South Africa and Germany and it is the lowest for France, USA and Italy.
